Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock scored 114 runs and Rassie van der Dussen scored 133 runs for South Africa
Marco Jansen took 3 wickets for 31 runs
Keshav Maharaj took 4 wickets for 46 runs
Glenn Phillips scored 60 runs for New Zealand
Tim Southee took 2 wickets for 77 runs
South Africa posted 357 runs and dismissed New Zealand for 167 runs
The match resulted in a 190-run victory for South Africa
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa captain Temba Bavuma praised the team's performance, mentioning their handling of the challenge up front and sustaining pressure throughout New Zealand's innings
New Zealand captain Tom Latham expressed disappointment, saying their team struggled to build partnerships after being three or four down early in the innings
Miscellaneous Highlights: Quinton de Kock will retire from the 50-over format after the tournament
Matt Henry was ruled out of the match due to a right hamstring problem
Jimmy Neesham was struck on the hand while stopping a ball off his own bowling but did not suffer broken bones
